{{Quote
|To dispense fouled water, merely lift the bucket and fling the liquid into the street.
|''[[Aurora]], explaining the mechanics of a bucket''
}}
* Buckets were extremely useful for carrying water, and also served as excellent receptacles for other materials as needed.
* Some kept buckets of water near their jake, sometimes scented so as to stave away stagnant odor, to flush their waste down.{{Cite web/Elminster Speaks/Part 17: A Place to Stay}}
